'It [the new contract] is deserved and I'm really happy for him.'

The pair spent eight seasons together at Stamford Bridge before Drogba moved to Galatasaray in 2012 but were reunited when the former Ivory Coast international rejoined the club this summer. 

Drogba and Terry have won three Premier League titles, four FA Cups and three League Cups together at Chelsea as well as the Champions League in 2012 as Drogba dispatched the winning spot-kick against Bayern Munich.

